cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC

The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for automated seizure detection in electroencephalograms (EEGs). This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory networks (LSTMs) to analyze the spatial and temporal contexts of the EEG signals. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of CNNs also suggests a possible association with cs.CV (Computer Vision), while the focus on clinical applications suggests a possible association with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
